p: AIC values for the two chosen multivariate models as well as all candidate models and the univariate models are presented in Additional file 1: Table S1. Additional diagnostic criteria including the white noise test and partial auto-correlation functions for each model are presented in Additional file 1: Figures S2 and S3. Residuals plots are presented in Additional file 1: Figures S4 and S5, and showed that the models tended to over-predict at low case counts and under-predict at high counts. Lastly, Additional file 1: Table S2 presents zero mean test results, allowing us to affirm that no unit root exists and that the data series used in this analysis is stationary.
